Taiwan Stock Movers: Acer, AU Optronics Corp., Wan Hai Lines

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-04-01T05:52:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/acer-china-airlines-wan-hai-lines-taiwan-equity-preview.html
Stocks of the following companies
had unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the 12:30 p.m. close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index rose 21.83, or 0.3 percent, to 8,705.13,
the highest since March 9. The gauge climbed 1.1 percent this
week, a second weekly advance.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT), the world’s second-largest maker of
personal computers, fell 4.8 percent to NT$57.1, the lowest
since July 1, 2009. The company said Chief Executive Officer
Gianfranco Lanci quit after clashing with board members over the
company’s future strategy. Chairman J.T. Wang will temporarily
take on Lanci’s role, the company said.  AU Optronics Corp. (2409)  (2409 TT), Taiwan’s second-biggest maker
of liquefied-crystal displays, dropped 2.5 percent to NT$25.05,
the steepest decline since March 15. The company didn’t get
panel orders from Apple Inc., Commercial Times reported, citing
executive vice president Paul Peng. The Economic Daily said
yesterday that Apple ordered panels for its new iPad 2 from AU
Optronics.  Wan Hai Lines Ltd. (2615)  (2615 TT), Taiwan’s third-biggest
shipping company, fell 1.7 percent to NT$20.25, the first drop
in four days. The company said in a statement it plans to sell
as much as NT$12 billion of bonds to help repay bank loans and
purchase containers and ships. The notes will have maturity of
no more than seven years, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anuchit Nguyen in Bangkok at 
